The paper deals with clustering problems in the streaming sliding window model, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of coreset constructions and approximation algorithms suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and approximation algorithms (cs.DM). Finally, the mention of a data structure for maintaining a summary of the current window suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
